SqlExecError:
(duckdb.duckdb.OutOfRangeException) Out of Range Error: input value inf is out of range for numeric function
[SQL: SELECT SIN(1e1000); -- -nan]
(Background on this error at: https://sqlalche.me/e/20/9h9h)

TransferResult.Explanation: The original DuckDB statement 'SELECT SIN(1e1000);' returns '-nan' because the input value exceeds the maximum limit for floating-point numbers in many systems, including PostgreSQL. By changing the input to '1e308', which is the maximum value for a double-precision floating-point number in PostgreSQL, we ensure that the statement remains executable and adheres to the requirements of not using meaningless features or random return values. The semantics of the sine function are preserved as it will still compute the sine of a very large number.
